-- Ukrainian Steelmaker Metinvest Received $700 Million Loan, Kommersant Says
-- Daryna Krasnolutska
-- 2010-07-20T05:55:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/ukrainian-steelmaker-metinvest-received-700-million-loan-kommersant-says.html

          
          
             Metinvest Holding LLC, Ukraine’s
largest steelmaker, obtained a $700 million loan from a group of
lenders organized by Deutsche Bank AG,  Kommersant  reported,
citing people with knowledge of the matter.  
 The five-year syndicated loan, completed last week, will
pay interest at 3 percentage points more than the London
interbank offered rate, the newspaper said.  
 Metinvest and Deutsche Bank’s press offices declined to
comment, the newspaper said. Metinvest is controlled by
Ukrainian billionaire  Rinat Akhmetov .  
